pullRequest.bodyText:
This adds another script to tool/color to create a mapping for CupertinoColors to allow them to be shown in editor gutters:

The CupertinoColor class references quite a few other classes, so reusing its file as-is required creating quite a few empty stub classes (an alternative could be to make it a real Flutter app and use the SDK directly - which I think Icons already does - but I wasn't sure if that was overkill).
@devoncarew

